<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="438" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[101,1032,190,711]" pageId="25" pageNumber="438">
Comments. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bredd." box="[290,517,571,594]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Brachystethus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="438" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coxalis">
<emphasis box="[290,517,571,594]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="438">Brachystethus coxalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the sister group of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1851" box="[733,835,571,594]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Brachystethus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="438" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vicinus">
<emphasis box="[733,835,571,594]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="438">B. vicinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1905" box="[882,1025,571,594]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Brachystethus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="438" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="improvisus">
<emphasis box="[882,1025,571,594]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="438">B. improvisus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, sharing with them one synapomorphy, the yellowish tarsi, and two homoplastic characters, coxae, and apex of femora and base of tibiae yellowish (
